      • outsideOf

        public static <T extends Comparable<?>> Predicate<T> outsideOf(Range<T> range)
        Create a Predicate whose test(v) behaves like ! range.test(v)

        This can be useful in a situation such as filtering to include only values that are outside of a range. 

        
     TStream<?> outsideRange = readings.filter(Ranges.outsideOf(Ranges.open(10,20)));
        Type Parameters:
        T - Endpoint type
        Parameters:
        range - the Range
        Returns:
        the Predicate
